Q.6 --> What is the ‘class’ attribute in HTML? With Example.

Ans:- 
      
      -> The class is an attribute that specifies one or more class names for an HTML element.
      -> The class attribute can be used on any HTML element.
      -> The class name can be used by CSS and JavaScript to perform certain tasks for elements with the specified class name.

      Example: 
               
               <style>

                  h1.a
                  {
                  color: aqua;
                  }

                  p.a
                  {
                  color: gray;
                  }

                  p.b
                  {
                  color: red;
                  }

               </style>

            <body>

               <h1 class=a> Davda Utsav </h1>
               <p class=a> Hello, I Am Frontend Developer </p> 
               <p class=b> My Age Is: 19 

            </body>

